title: I have to stop.
body:
I have to go back to the time when I do not care - or I’m not even aware - what other people say about certain things. The latest example: Captain Marvel.

I am soooo excited for this movie, and I still am. My natural curiosity led me to read a few reviews here and there. Most of the reviews are positive and, of course, as with everything else, it is not a perfect movie so I accept that there are other reviews that didn’t like some parts of it for legit reasons.

What’s tiresome though is that this vocal minority, fueled by hate, push their opinions on others that genuinely like the movie. I’m sick of it. It’s not just for Captain Marvel. It also happens to other things I love like Iron Man 3 and Final Fantasy XV and XIII.

So, from now on, I will never care about what other people think. What I should care about is what I think. I’ll stop reading reviews and just see it for myself and formulate my own opinion.

summary: Lol this is enough to tell me I'm gonna like it- I'm really tired of movies about women focusing on how fucking different we...
body: Lol this is enough to tell me I’m gonna like it- I’m really tired of movies about women focusing on how fucking different we are. Just let her kick ass. It’s fine. She doesn’t need to cry all day about it or fall in love or whatever. We have a million billion woman centric movies about being vulnerable and needing romance and all that horse shit. Let me have my stupid comic book space alien pilot punching people and blowing stuff up.
